name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: The truth is "Individuals are at their best when they identify with a community and communities are ONLY at their best when they identify ALL of their individuals." We just have build an economic system that literally reflects our value(s), so you can make our community whole.

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: Data is our rare opportunity to couple what we all know to be true spiritually without using abstract terms like spirituality. Unlike the preacher who says you have favor, we say you have value and we can prove it. We're only valuable because you exist.

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: This sort of acknowledgment of value and authority triggers some rather obvious opportunities to shrink the wealth gap without stifling percieved incentives to build companies and solve problems. It also provides opportunities for digital data protection even in a dynamic world.

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: There are 5.3 Million profitable corporations in the US and they all make it based on our data, our culture, our interactions, our value. So my "American Value Act" establishes a #UBI using a #DataDividend because that'd actually be inclusive capitalism (#inclusionism)

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: Technology only exists in 3 forms: 1) Hardware (stuff we can touch) 2) Software (stuff we can't touch) 3) Methods (process we use) Corporations are legal processes for groups of us to remit value to each other after being incentivized to exist based on our data.

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: That's the logic behind a #UniversalBasicIncome and the reason you're owed it, and it's not a "Tech Check", is because tech is just an extension of humanity. It owes us everything. Every company owes us everything because even they are tech.

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: We only derive our value from interactions with each other. If we existed in an empty white space with no friction no transacting sweat and tears and information with each other, there'd be no value. Lastly, you're entitled to some of the value that we inherently give off.

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: You see, you can't "Opt-Out" of society or you'd cease to exist, further, you wouldn't have value. When I say in my #inclusionism theory that "you have intrinsic value" I mean it is a fact of life, or rather your life's interaction with other's lives.

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: A #DataDividend is an equity stake in the institutions of the society that thrives because it is knowledgeable about you. It's a base line payment for your participation, voluntary or involuntary. It must be universal.

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: Data is only valuable because it's a reflection of the individuals and institutions you interact with. So, it's also NOT something you can wholly own. It's something you want transacted so the world can acknowledge you. And for that achievement you are owed both authority & money

name: James Felton Keith II ‚â•
tweet: Data is everything, not just what you think FB has on you digitally. It's your DNA, Location, Insurance, Finance, & Social info. It's all the stuff you think you are and all the stuff the world thinks you are. Data is the new matter. We're attaching a data point to all matter.
